wikipedia_page.main: Marjorie Browne (1910–1990) was a British musical theatre actress who made occasional films.Her West End appearances included the original productions of Cole Porter's Wake Up and Dream at the London Pavilion in 1929; Stanley Lupino's  musical Sporting Love at the Gaiety in 1934; and as Marjanah in the revival of Chu Chin Chow at the Palace in 1940.
